A member of the House of Representatives, representing Ikorodu Federal Constituency, Babajimi Benson, in conjunction with a non-governmental organisation, We Stand Foundation, has donated food items to 300 beneficiaries to in the Ikorodu area of Lagos State. Benson said the project, which was done through his iCare FoodBank initiative, was in line with one of the sustainable development goals of eradicating poverty in the country. He said: “One of the SDG goals is to eradicate poverty and if we are not striving towards eradicating poverty, then we are not doing good governance. So, we provided this kind of project to enable our people to enjoy the dividends of democracy.” VSO trains youth on peace promotion in Ikorodu Why farmers target festive periods to sell layer birds Christmas: NGO distributes food items to widows in Suleja